deck: British-American Writer of Smoke and its sequel, Ashes, as well as Grindhouse: Doors Open at Midnight.
description: Alex de Campi is a Princeton-educated writer and music video director. She directed the video for Amanda Palmer's "Leeds United." Currently, she is writing Grindhouse: Doors Open at Midnight for Dark Horse, who have also repackaged her Eisner-nominated limited series, Smoke (originally published by IDW). de Campi splits her time between the United States and the United Kingdom.

deck: Akira Miyashita is a quite possibly one of the most famous Japanese manga authors of all time. His first series to date is about young men training to be come elite gangsters in a Yakuza school entitled "Shiritsu Kiwamemichi Koukou" (Ultimate Path Private High School). It was publicized in the Jump Comics magazine in 1979. But due to a scandal linking to the series it was cancelled indefinitely. Miyashita's most notable work to date is his work on his manga series entitled "Sakigake!! Otokojuku".
name: Akira Miyashita
